{{Infobox Governor |honorific-prefix = |name = Francisco Javier Gaxiola |honorific-suffix = |image = Francisco Javier Gaxiola.jpg |order = <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by adding a number--> |office = [[Governor of the State of Mexico]] |term_start = September 11, 1919 |term_end = March 8, 1920 ''(acting)'' |lieutenant = <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by adding a number--> |predecessor = [[Agustín Millán Vivero]] |successor = [[Agustín Millán Vivero]] |president = [[Venustiano Carranza]] |birth_date = {{birth date|1870|1|31}} |birth_place = [[Sinaloa de Leyva]] |death_date = {{death date and age|1933|11|18|1870|1|31}} |death_place = [[Mexico City]] |restingplace = |restingplacecoordinates = |birthname = |nationality = [[Mexico|Mexican]] |party = |otherparty = <!--For additional political affiliations--> |spouse = |partner = <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married--> |relations = |children = |residence = |alma_mater = |occupation = |profession = lawyer, politician, diplomat |cabinet = |committees = |portfolio = |religion = |signature = |website = |footnotes = |blank1 = |data1 = |blank2 = |data2 = |blank3 = |data3 = |blank4 = |data4 = |blank5 = |data5 = <!--Military service--> |nickname = |allegiance = |branch = |serviceyears = |rank = |unit = |commands = |battles = |awards = |military_blank1 = |military_data1 = |military_blank2 = |military_data2 = |military_blank3 = |military_data3 = |military_blank4 = |military_data4 = |military_blank5 = |military_data5 = }}
'''Francisco Javier Gaxiola Castillo-Negrete'''<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Ldt-5A1Q7akC&pg=PA52&lpg=PA52&dq=%22Francisco+Javier+Gaxiola%22+1933&source=bl&ots=sGEa6uN3ZG&sig=O0FTfiRPsOel1Y9eIFGVaFtaVZw&hl=de&ei=1f0rSr3HJ8-usAbD8tWeDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5 ''Panorama mexicano 1890-1910''] (Spanish), 2006, p. 52.</ref> (January 31, 1870 in [[Sinaloa de Leyva]] &ndash; November 18, 1933 in [[Mexico City]]<ref>C. Valadés: [https://books.google.com/books?id=wOMj4_QZPjsC&pg=PR11&lpg=PR11&dq=%22Francisco+javier+Gaxiola%22+1870+%22de+1933%22&source=bl&ots=zof_opV2bv&sig=lpMKo3Gy7BSjHX9Xf7KcZBbMB2Q&hl=de&ei=HfErSvbKNouO_QaIwOCKCw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5 ''Obras''] (Spanish), 1992, p. XI.</ref>) was a [[Mexico|Mexican]] lawyer, politician and diplomat.
Gaxiola taught in superior-level institutions of law in the [[Estado de México]]. As diplomat he was adviser of the Legation of Mexico in Madrid.<ref>José de J. Núñez y Domínguez: [http://biblioteca.universia.net/ficha.do?id=37908825 ''Semblanza biográfica del señor licenciado F. Javier Gaxiola''] (Spanish).</ref> From September 11, 1919, to March 8, 1920, he was acting [[Governor of the State of Mexico]],<ref>[http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Mexico_states2.html ''States of Mexico M-Z - México (Estado de México)'']</ref> while [[Agustín Millán Vivero]], the original governor, accompanied President [[Venustiano Carranza]], when the [[Plan of Agua Prieta|rebellion in Agua Prieta]] exploded.<ref>Gerardo Novo Valencia: [http://www.oem.com.mx/elsoldetoluca/notas/s759.htm ''El centro deportivo Agustín Millán''] (Spanish), October 22, 2007.</ref>
