{{BLP sources|date=March 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Joanna Taylor | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1978|07|24}} | birth_place = [[Tooting]], [[South London]], [[England]] | other_names = Joanna Clark | occupation = [[Actress]] | years_active = 1995–present | spouse = [[Danny Murphy (footballer, born 1977)|Danny Murphy]] (2004–present) | children = 2 }}
'''Joanna Taylor''' (born 24 July 1978) is an English actress and former model.
==Early life and career== Born in [[Tooting]], [[South London]], Taylor was a student at the [[Guildford School of Acting]]. Her big break came in 1999, when she won the role of [[Geri Hudson]] in [[Channel 4]] teen [[soap opera|soap]] ''[[Hollyoaks]]''. She left in 2001, and has since starred in [[BBC One]] [[Policing in the United Kingdom|police]] drama, ''[[Merseybeat (TV series)|Merseybeat]]'' as [[Constable|PC]] Jackie Brown. In 2004, Taylor appeared in the American film ''[[Post Impact]]'' with [[Dean Cain]]. In 2005, Taylor turned to writing, contributing a weekly [[column (newspaper)|column]] to [[The Times]] from the perspective of a "[[WAGs|footballer's wife]]" and in 2007, after taking an extended break from [[acting]], she featured in the British independent film ''[[Back in Business (2007 film)|Back in Business]]'', opposite [[Martin Kemp]].
==Personal life== Taylor married [[England national football team|English]] [[football (soccer)|footballer]] [[Danny Murphy (footballer, born 1977)|Danny Murphy]] on 7 July 2004, whom she met through mutual actor friend [[Louis Emerick]] in [[Barbados]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/news/article1152657.ece | title = My Danny played a blinder ... as a loving dad and husband | work = [[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]] | date = 2008-05-12 | accessdate = 2008-05-12}}</ref> They have a daughter and Taylor is step-mother to Murphy's son from a previous relationship. Taylor took part in the 2007 Great South Run for children's cancer charity [[CLIC Sargent]].
