'''Jože Humer''' (24 June 1936 – 13 June 2012) was a [[Slovenia]]n [[composer]], choirmaster, [[lyricist]], translator, and cultural organiser.<ref name="RTV2012-03-16" /> He was born in [[Maribor]], attended a local [[classical gymnasium]], and then studied and graduated from law.<ref name="JSKD1999" /> He established the [[Ljubljana Madrigalists Chamber Choir]] and led the [[Tone Tomšič Academic Choir]] and the [[Gallus Octet]] in Ljubljana. He was president of the [[Ljubljana Musical Youth]], the renovator of the [[Ljubljana Musical Society]], and president of the [[Association of Cultural Organisations of Slovenia]]. He wrote and translated hundreds of [[libretto]]s and other lyrics for children, choirs, and soloists. In 1999, he received the Golden Medal of the [[Slovenian Public Fund of Cultural Activities]] for his work.<ref name="JSKD1999">{{cite web |url=http://www.jskd.si/priznanja-in-nagrade/nagrajenci_priznanja_1999.htm |title=Priznanja sklada za leto 1999: Jože Humer |language=Slovenian |trans-title=1999 Recognitions of the Fund: Jože Humer |accessdate=13 June 2012}}</ref> He was also a judge, a secretary of the [[Supreme Court of Slovenia]],<ref name="JSKD1999" /> and involved in the legal and organisational arrangements in the field of culture in the 1980s and during [[Slovenian secession from Yugoslavia]].<ref name="RTV2012-03-16" /> Later, he collaborated as an expert with the [[Slovenian Constitutional Court]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rtvslo.si/kultura/drugo/umrl-je-joze-humer-glasbena-dusa-in-strasten-kulturni-delavec/285216 |title=Umrl je Jože Humer, glasbena duša in strasten kulturni delavec |language=Slovenian |trans-title=Jože Humer, Musical Soul and Passionate Cultural Worker, Has Died |work=MMC RTV Slovenija |publisher=RTV Slovenija |date=13 June 2012}}</ref> In March 2012, he was decorated by Slovenian President [[Danilo Türk]] with the [[Order for Merits (Slovenia)|Order for Merits of Slovenia]], with a rationale that described him as an "above-average deserving personality of the Slovenian cultural life."<ref name="RTV2012-03-16">{{cite news |url=http://www.rtvslo.si/kultura/drugo/predsednik-tuerk-je-odlikoval-kulturniskega-aktivista-humra-in-vsestranskega-jurgca/279088 |title=Predsednik Türk je odlikoval kulturniškega aktivista Humra in vsestranskega Jurgca |language=Slovenian |trans-title=The President Türk Decorated the Cultural Activist Humer and the Versatile Jurgec |work=MMC RTV Slovenija |publisher=RTV Slovenija |date=16 March 2012}}</ref>
