'''P.S. Arjun''' (born 19 November 1982) is an [[List of Indian film directors|Indian film director]] and writer who works in [[Tamil cinema]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Amutha Movie: Showtimes, Review, Trailer, Posters, News & Videos {{!}} eTimes|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-details/amutha/movieshow/63379141.cms|accessdate=2018-04-11}}</ref> He is directing a Tamil [[Music genre|musical]] [[Psychological thriller]] film titled [[Amutha]] with Sriya Sree in the lead and Anees Shaz, Levin Simon Joseph, Ashna Sudheer and Shivakumar Raju in important characters.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.maalaimalar.com/amp/Cinema/CinemaNews/2018/03/26165622/1153303/Amutha-a-film-inspired-from-Kannathil-Muthamittal.vpf|title=Kannathil Muthamittal, Amutha, கன்னத்தில் முத்தமிட்டால், அமுதா|work=Maalaimalar|access-date=2018-04-11|language=TA-IN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.plumeriamovies.com/psarjun-amutha-2018-tamil-movie/|title=Amutha (2018) Tamil Movie|date=2018-01-05|work=Plumeria Movies|access-date=2018-04-11|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/040418/title-inspired-by-character-in-mani-ratnam-movie.html|title=Title inspired by character in Mani Ratnam movie|date=2018-04-04|work=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/|access-date=2018-04-09|language=en}}</ref>

Arjun worked with [[Infosys BPM|Infosys BPO]], [[Bangalore]] as an HR professional and ING Vysya Insurance, [[Chennai]] as an Operation Executive before leaving to pursue his dream of becoming a movie director. His love for [[Tamil cinema|Tamil movies]] sprouted after watching movies like [[Roja]] and [[Gentleman (1993 film)|Gentleman]]. His interest on movies became serious after watching [[Kannathil Muthamittal]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/310818/all-about-the-chills.html|title=All about the chills|date=2018-08-31|work=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en}}</ref>.

